[TOC(start:2 end:2)]



The **Navmesh** map in Content Example provides three examples of how to generate and use a **NavMesh** to enable **Pawns** the ability to pathfind their way through obstacles, over ramps or to jump off ledges. While in the editor, and with a **NavMeshBoundsVolume** placed in the level, pressing the **P** key will show/hide the area that the NavMesh covers. The final example in this map shows how the coverage area of a NavMesh is automatically updated when moving **Actors** around in the level (this can be disabled via the **Editor Settings** under **Level Editor/Miscellaneous** and unchecking the **Update Navigation Automatically** checkbox). 

[region:note]
You can find additional resources for each example by clicking on the example's name.
[/region]
 

## Navmesh Map

![](NavMesh_Map.png)(w:640)

Listed below are the examples provided inside the **Navmesh** map:

| Example | What is Demonstrated |
| ------- | ------------ |
| **[1.1 Simple navigation around obstacles](Resources\ContentExamples\NavMesh\1_1)** | How to get a Pawn to navigate through a set of obstacles. |
| **[1.2 Navigation using a Nav Link Proxy](Resources\ContentExamples\NavMesh\1_2)** | Shows a Pawn navigating up to and jumping off a ramp. |
| **[1.3 Navmesh rebuild after moving Actors](Resources\ContentExamples\NavMesh\1_3)** | This example demonstrates how the NavMesh automatically updates when Actors like Static Meshes are moved in the editor. |





